The waitress who "welcomed" us told us that the kitchen was already closed. My girlfriend explained to her that we did see that the restaurant closes at 11.00 pm, but she reiterated that the kitchen closes half an hour before the closing time of the restaurant, whilst literally shutting the door behind us and griming at her colleague. Leaving the place, I immediately checked Uber Eats to see if the kitchen was in fact closed, and it confirmed that the kitchen was still open for another 20 minutes.
This used to be my favourite restaurant when I was living in London, and it hurt me to see what it became.

name: Runako “Grizzly” Williams
text:
Ordered at 6.30pm, got a notification that the food was on its way at 7pm , at 7.40pm food still had not arrived! I then called the restaurant and spoke with manager, Karlota or Carlotta, she said her name was,  who said the food should be here shortly. At 7.55pm somebody claiming to be driver called me and said he was outside. I went straight outside as I was still on the phone and hadn’t seen anybody walk into my gate. The person hung up I called back 27times and sent numerous text messages asking where are you I am outside. I then called the restaurant back which took 20 mins to get through to. They then told me that I told the driver I had cancelled and I was not coming downstairs, which is a lie because for one I live on the ground floor and for two the driver never ever arrived at my property. I gave the manager the drivers number, she said that’s not her drivers number, I’m lying I must have made orders with someone else aswell. She said she would call back and when she did the story had changed that the driver said he knocked the window numerous times and nobody answered, the window was open curtains were open. He would have seen me and my partner sitting there if he had arrived and spoken to me.

She then proceeded to shout over me saying she will send back the cold food from the restaurant as she will not be re-cooking it because we should have answered the door.

We are Regular customer and have never experienced this with Slurp in the almost 8 years we have ordered from them. Just for the level of attitude and disrespect I have lost all respect for the company and I will never I mean NEVER EVER order from them again as long I walk the Earth.
title: Slurp

address: 104-106 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BW, United Kingdom
name: John Bishop
text:
Nice ambience with both bench and table seating. Service was efficient and quick.
Good size portions and the first mouthful took me back to the taste of local food in Thailand. A definite recommendation in itself. My tasty vegetarian rice dish was served in a wooden box that kept it hot throughout the meal.
Unfortunately there were few pure vegetarian choices (some of the choices are helpfully flagged up on the menu with a symbol denoting the presence of fish/shrimp in the cooking), only one or two if you don't want spicy food.
Despite the above, I would go back again to eat. I went on a whim, sat down, ordered food, food came, it was good, very satisfying, paid and left. Exactly what I wanted.
Not a place for an intimate date over a lingering meal but good place to grab a meal.

address: 104-106 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BW, United Kingdom
name: John Cheshire
text:
Great value and very tasty lunch.
I met my sister for lunch here. Her idea, I had not heard of Slurp before.
Midday, weekday it was quiet but nice place to chat over lunch.
Quite a lot of ramen on offer but that's not my thing. I am very much a Singapore noodles guy so ordered them. My noodles were delicious with a really satisfying chilli heat. Plenty of mixed meat with the noodles.
I had the Slurp mixed juice with the noodles, £8 lunch combination. The juice was refreshing and tasty.
My sister has suggested the nearby Wimpy as our next lunch meet. Wimpy would bring memories back but I will always be ready to revisit Slurp.
title: Slurp

address: 104-106 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BW, United Kingdom
name: John Edwards
text:
I have been to the Slurp restaurant several times before and recommended it to family and friends, mainly because I have generally been happy with the food. The service, however, has always been indifferent, a bit hit and miss, where the staff sometimes forget part of your order or they lack a reasonable level of good quality service, almost to the point where you have to show them what to do, (all in good spirit) i.e. a right handed person serving you on your left side and exposing you to their arm pit and smelling body odor (ghastly stuff).

My last two visits have been worrying in that having ordered rice (among other things) and upon eating it found that it was not right, the texture was spongy and it had no taste. I had to return it on both occasions. The Manager (male) apologized, removed it from the bill and brought a dessert as a gesture free of charge (good man). It is because of the manager and his desire to provide good service if things go wrong, the reason why I returned to this restaurant.

My most recent visit, however, was a disaster. The manager was not there on this occasion and all hell broke loose. I made my usual order but the rice was just not right. I literally only ate 2 or 3 small bite size portions for taste and it was just spongy with little or no taste. I asked the waitress (black girl) to take it away.

When I received the bill, the Chinese lady who appeared to be in charge insisted I pay for the rice because she claimed I had eaten over half of it.This was simply not true and she was clearly 'reaching'. She then called the waitress (black girl) who became animated and shouted at me saying I've returned the rice on 2 previous occasions, which only endorsed my previous concerns that perhaps there is something wrong or something more sinister with the rice.

But what was most outrageous and completely unacceptable was not only what was being said to me by both staff members, but the sheer aggression and ignorant manner they exhibited. They stood over me whilst I was sitting at the table and shouted in ear shot of other guests saying I must pay for the rice. I was utterly shocked and numb by their behavior. I felt bullied and utterly humiliated. I was given the option of paying the full bill or told not to come back. Needless to say, I will not be going back and will be informing my family and friends of this incident. You may like the rice, I didn't.

Visited February 2017

address: 104-106 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BW, United Kingdom
name: Charlotte Hilton
text: My partner and I often pop in here for lunch and love it. He always goes for the house ramen and asks for a some additional chopped chilli to be added, for a bit of warmth (don't eat them, just let them add flavor to the broth). I always go for the salmon teriyaki bento box, which offers loads of variations in flavors and textures. The staff are always friendly and have no problem with making the minor alterations that we request for our meals (more of this, less/non of that). He also sometime buys the salt and pepper squid as a side, which is great. If you're a fan of fruit drinks, ask for the Slurp juice.

name: Greg Burke
text:
A buzzing restaurant on Streatham's High Road.

If you've ever been to a Wagamama's then you'll be familiar with the concept. Expect good value Chinese, Thai and Japanese dishes served with a smile by friendly staff.

It looks a little bit like a nightclub from the outside, but don't be fooled, it's a great local restaurant if you're after some cheap eats.
